{{Infobox journal | title = Biology and Philosophy | cover = | editor = [[Michael Weisberg]] | discipline = [[Philosophy of biology]] | peer-reviewed = | language = English | former_names = | abbreviation = Biol. Philos. | publisher = [[Springer Science+Business Media|Springer]] | country = | frequency = Bimonthly | history = 1986–Present | openaccess = | license = | impact = 1.209 | impact-year = 2016 | website = https://www.springer.com/philosophy/epistemology+and+philosophy+of+science/journal/10539 | OCLC = 13073787 | LCCN = 86642996 | CODEN = BIOPEI | ISSN = 0169-3867 | eISSN = 1572-8404 | boxwidth = }}
'''''Biology and Philosophy''''' is a [[peer-review]]ed [[academic journal]] that publishes articles about [[philosophy of biology]], broadly understood to span conceptual, theoretical, and methodological issues in the biological sciences.
The journal was founded by [[Michael Ruse]] in 1986,<ref>{{cite encyclopedia |last=Griffiths |first=Paul |date=4 July 2008 |title=Philosophy of Biology |url=http://plato.stanford.edu/entries/biology-philosophy/ |encyclopedia=[[Stanford Encyclopedia of Philosophy]] |accessdate=2012-08-29 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Ross |first=Gregg |title=An interview with Michael Ruse |url=http://www.americanscientist.org/bookshelf/pub/michael-ruse |work=[[American Scientist]] |accessdate=2012-08-29 }}</ref> edited by him from 1986 to 2000, then edited by [[Kim Sterelny]] from 2000 to 2016,<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Sterelny|first=Kim|date=2017-01-01|title=Farewell|url=https://link.springer.com/article/10.1007/s10539-016-9559-6|journal=Biology & Philosophy|language=en|volume=32|issue=1|pages=1–3|doi=10.1007/s10539-016-9559-6|issn=0169-3867}}</ref> and it is currently edited by [[Michael Weisberg]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Biology and Philosophy (Editorial Board) |url=https://www.springer.com/philosophy/epistemology+and+philosophy+of+science/journal/10539?detailsPage=editorialBoard |publisher=[[Springer Science+Business Media|Springer]] |accessdate=2017-01-09 }}</ref> It is published by [[Springer Science+Business Media|Springer]].
==Abstracting and indexing== The journal is abstracted and indexed in the following databases {{columns-list|colwidth=22em| *[[Academic OneFile]] *[[Academic Search]] *[[Arts & Humanities Citation Index]] *[[Biological Abstracts]] *[[BIOSIS]] *[[Current Abstracts]] *[[Current Contents]]/Arts and Humanities *[[Dietrich's Index Philosophicus]] *[[EBSCO]] *[[EMBiology]] *[[European Route of Industrial Heritage|ERIH]] *[[Gale]] *[[Geobase]] *[[International Bibliography of Book Reviews]] *[[International Bibliography of Periodical Literature]] *[[ISIS Current Bibliography of the History of Science]] *[[OmniFile]] *[[Répertoire Bibliographique de la Philosophie]] *[[Science Citation Index]] *[[Journal Citation Reports]]/Science Edition *[[Journal Citation Reports]]/Social Sciences Edition *[[Social Science Citation Index]] *[[Social SciSearch]] *[[SCOPUS]] *[[Science Select]] *[[SCImago]] *[[Summon by Serial Solutions]] *[[The Philosopher's Index]] *[[Zoological Record]] }}
Its 2011 [[impact factor]] was 1.203.
