{{Infobox religious building | name = Mount Baldy Zen Center | native_name = | image = Mount Baldy Zen Center Mounatin View.jpg | image_size = | alt = | caption = | map_type = | map_size = | map_alt = | map_caption = | location = P.O. Box 429 Mount Baldy, CA 91759 | coordinates = | religious_affiliation = [[Rinzai]] | deity = | country = [[United States]] | functional_status = | website = [http://www.mbzc.org/ http://www.mbzc.org/] | founded_by = [[Kyozan Joshu Sasaki]] | year_completed = 1971 }} '''Mount Baldy Zen Center''' (MBZC) is a [[Rinzai]] Zen [[monastery]] of the Nyorai-nyokyo sect, located in the [[San Gabriel Mountains]] of the [[Angeles National Forest]] region on {{convert|4.5|acre|m2}} and founded in 1971 by [[Kyozan Joshu Sasaki]]. The monastery — once a [[Boy Scout]] camp — became famous when [[musician]] [[Leonard Cohen]] joined the community in 1994. The monastery served as residence for [[Kyozan_Joshu_Sasaki|Sasaki]], and is the training center for monastics in his lineage. Other centers in Sasaki's network, including Rinzai-ji, offer the opportunity to practice [[Zen]] to [[Laity|laypeople]] in the lineage. Sasaki died in 2014 at the age of 107.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2014/08/05/us/joshu-sasaki-a-zen-master-tarnished-by-abuse-claims-dies-at-107.html|title=Joshu Sasaki, 107, Tainted Zen Master|date=4 Aug 2014|work=[[The New York Times]]|accessdate=31 January 2015}}</ref>
