'''Sholom Gherman''' (born 1920) is a philosopher from [[Russia]].

Gherman graduated from [[Leningrad State University]] with an MA in Philosophy. From there, he taught philosophy in "higher schools of art", according to his biography in the 1967 book ''[[Socialism: Theory and Practice]]''.<ref>{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=asc1AQAAIAAJ&q=%22Sholom+Gherman%22&dq=%22Sholom+Gherman%22&hl=en&ei=RvTcTeW4AYXX8gO1y_DpDw&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=2&ved=0CC8Q6AEwAQ|title=Socialism, theory and practice , Volume 13|publisher=Novosti Press Agency Pub. House|accessdate=25 May 2011}}</ref> He also published several other books of philosophy and theory of art.

